misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that when printing array elements followed by a separator (like a space), the conditional logic (`if(i!=n-1)`) used to avoid printing a trailing separator inside the loop also correctly handles all necessary spacing between elements.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: The student correctly implements the common pattern of avoiding a trailing separator. However, they failed to place the necessary space separator within the conditional block (`if (i != n - 1) System.out.print(" ");`) or ensure a space follows the element printout. Currently, they print the element and then conditionally print a space, but they should ensure a space is always printed unless it's the very last element being printed, which means the space needs to be included.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: Wrong output formatting (elements are concatenated without spaces).
